<item>
            <title>[KAFKA-3486] Autocommit does not execute periodically when partitions are manually assigned</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-3486</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;We have an internal periodic task to commit offsets when autocommit is enabled, but we only start it after the consumer has joined its group. When the user is using manual partition assignment through assign(), the autocommit task never gets started, so the only time offsets would be committed is in close().&lt;/p&gt;</description>
